g.text: Goal: To ensure each subject is in a stable state.1)For each subject in each entered feature (biomarker), outliers are defined using the median absolute deviation (MAD).2)The non-parametric Mann-Kendall test is also done to ensure no monotonic trendspresent in each subject.3)Variance in each time series: the variance should remain stable in each time series.
IRIs are computed for the remaining stable-subjects.
